Package: JPselect
Type: Package
Title: Just-Pope Production Functions with Heckman Selectivity Correction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Roberto", family = "Cardenas Retamal",
                  email = "roberto.cardenasret@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimate Just-Pope (1978, 1979) stochastic production functions
    with a two-step Heckman (1979) correction for sample selection in
    crop choice, following Koundouri and Nauges (2005, JARE 30(3):597-608).
    Provides the three-step procedure end-to-end: (1) probit selection
    equation and inverse Mills ratio, (2) linear-quadratic mean production
    function, (3) Cobb-Douglas variance (risk) function on log absolute
    residuals. Standard errors are obtained by a full-pipeline bootstrap.
    Convenience methods print, summarise, and plot the with-vs-without
    selectivity comparison that is the headline result of the paper.
